How to run Python-Tetris?

----------
1. Make sure you have pygame installed, if not, install it. Simple instructions are provited here.
You can find more information on: www.pygame.org/wiki/GettingStarted#Further%20info%20on%20installation

via Python:
$ python3 -m pip install -U pygame --user

Debian-based:
$ sudo apt-get install python3-pygame

Raspbian:
Pygame is installed out of the box, but it's some old version. To install newer one, you can run:
$ python3 -m pip install -U pygame --user

Fedora/RHEL
$ sudo yum install python3-pygame

Arch-based
$ sudo pamac install python-pygame
(note that it's "pamac", not "pacman" and also that according to various sources, you should not run pamac with root privileges)

OpenSUSE:
$ sudo zypper install python3-pygame

---
For bad experience:
---
Mac OS:
python3 -m pip install -U pygame --user

Windows:
py -m pip install -U pygame --user


----------
2. To run programs

cd in terminal to the right directory and run Tetris with
$ python3 Tetris_0.2.py

You can also compile this and make it executable so you don't need python or pygame installed
